news.title: ED attaches Sanskar Group's flats, villa in Goa and Delhi
news.para: "The attached assets are in the form of villas and flats in Goa, flats and office space in Delhi and Faridabad, and fixed deposits," the Enforcement Directorate (ED) said in a statement.

news.title: Over 90% land acquired for Ahmedabad-Mumbai bullet train project: NHSRCL
news.para: ​Railway Minister Ashwini Vaishnaw reviewed the progress of the project in Surat and Navsari districts of Gujarat on Monday and said he was confident that the first train will start running run between Surat and Bilimora in the state in 2026.

news.title: SC directs production of ex-CMD of Amrapali Group before AIIMS board for examination for surgery
news.para: A vacation bench of Justices MR Shah and Aniruddha Bose was told by advocate Manoj Singh, appearing for Sharma, that as per the medical advice he needs to be operated and for that, he needs to be produced before the doctors for examination and fixing of a date for the surgery.

news.title: Ghaziabad development body unable to get back land worth Rs 500 crore from squatters
news.para: Into his second stint as chief minister too, Yogi Adityanath is keen on carrying the impression of the "bulldozer baba" image bent on cracking down on the land mafia.

news.title: Kamdhenu rallies 12% as NCLT approves demerger of paint business
news.para: Kamdhenu Colour and Coatings Limited will be listed separately as the second resulting company, the building material maker's regulatory filing added.

news.title: Saudi Arabia: Retal Urban Development prices IPO at top of range
news.para: The book-building process generated orders of 90.3 billion riyals, in a sign of strong momentum for Saudi Arabia's IPO market that has defied the global trend.

news.title: Thiruvananthapuram: 94 families to be affected by Varkala bypass project
news.para: The project will require acquisition of 2.04 hectares of land. The road will run through Chaluvila, Kollamkonam, Cherukunnam and Sivagiri wards in Varkala municipality.

news.title: Cidco continues to levy service charges on housing societies in PCMC jurisdiction
news.para: The issue has remained unresolved, as Cidco has claimed that an outstanding service tax of around Rs 400 crore needs to be recovered from societies in PCMC jurisdiction.

news.title: Institutions bet big money on real estate projects in smaller cities
news.para: New Delhi-based real estate developer Omaxe recently raised ₹440 crore from Varde Partners, a global alternative investment firm, for expediting construction and delivery of its projects as well as investment into new projects.

news.title: RBI had questions about home loan agreement between HDFC and HDFC Bank
news.para: The regulator had been bringing up the issue of the unique agreement between HDFC and HDFC Bank over a period as it thought the arrangement was not good for the industry from the structure as well as the risk point of view, claimed the three people who did not want to be identified.

news.title: Partial takeover of Indirapuram by Ghaziabad civic body likely next month
news.para: Both the GMC and the Ghaziabad Development Authority (GDA) are these days busy preparing the separate estimates of the three services — horticulture, streetlights and sanitation — that will be handed over to the former by the latter, TOI has learnt.

news.title: Chandigarh civic body asks UT departments to purchase recycled concrete, material from C&D plant
news.para: Since this segment is also the part of the city’s C&D waste policy, all the departments will have to ensure purchase and consistent use in construction works.

news.title: Telangana: Plan to offer 2-BHK houses to over 12,000 nala squatters
news.para: The municipal administration department has been facing a major problem in removing over 12,000 squatters on major nalas in the city.

news.title: Flaw in Ahmedabad civic body's digital payments system?
news.para: ​Revenue committee chairman of the Ahmedabad Municipal Corporation (AMC) Jainik Vakil sought a detailed investigation, including a police complaint.

news.title: Goa town planning minister promises a list of violators on June 6
news.para: Rane also said that the TCP board will take a decision at its next board meeting to revert all illegally converted eco-sensitive land to its earlier status.
